                        <Section Name="MLSetupSection" FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11" Foreground="#BDBDBD">

                            <Paragraph>
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">ML MODELS SETUP</Run>
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph>
                                The ML MODELS Application creates custom Auto ML Models in four easy steps.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph>
                                You don't need machine learning expertise to use ML MODELS. All you need to do is: determine what you want to forecast (either Price or Volatility), select your training features, add some data, and hit the &quot;Train&quot; button.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <List>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph>
                                        Pick the Assets you want to train
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph>
                                        Add some data
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph>
                                        Determine what you want to forecast (either Price or Volatility)
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph>
                                        Select your training features
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph>
                                        And hit the &quot;Train&quot; button
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                            </List>

                            <Paragraph>
                                Once constructed and trained, ML MODELS automatically deploys Your ML Model to each ATM Application.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="0,30,0,0">
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">STEP 1 :</Run>
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph>
                                Add a new Model by selecting the
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">ADD NEW</Run>
                                Button.  Or select one from your list.  Model names can be changed by highlighting – then deleting the title - and typing a new one.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="0,30,0,0">
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">STEP 2 : MODEL SETUP</Run>
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="20,15,0,0">
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">SECURITIES</Run>
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="20,15,0,0">
                                Select the Assets you wish to train. The ATM ML Application provides an extensive list of Security List to choose.  Also, you can use Your EQS list or a PRTU.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="20,15,0,0">
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">SCENARIO</Run>
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="20,15,0,0">
                                Select between Future Price Forecast to Past Price References OR Volatility Increasing | Decreasing over various time horizons.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="20,15,0,0">
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">METRIC</Run>
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="20,15,0,0">
                                How your Model will be measured.  Choices are:
                            </Paragraph>

                            <List Margin="20,15,0,0">
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph>
                                        ACCURACY
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph>
                                        AUC
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph>
                                        AUCPR
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph>
                                        F1-Score
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                            </List>

                            <Paragraph Margin="20,15,0,0">
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">MAX TIME</Run>
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="20,15,0,0">
                                The amount of time to train Your Group or Each Individual Security.  Max Time is also multiplied by the number of Intervals chosen for your Model.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <List Margin="20,15,0,0">
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph>
                                        DataSet - 0 - 10 mb 10 Sec
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph>
                                        DataSet - 10 - 100 mb 10 Min
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph>
                                        DataSet - 100 - 500 mb 30 Min
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph>
                                        DataSet - 500 - 1 gb 60 Min
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph>
                                        DataSet - 1+ gb 3 hours +
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                            </List>

                            <Paragraph Margin="20,15,0,0">
                                The exact time to train also depends on:
                            </Paragraph>

                            <List Margin="20,15,0,0">
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph>
                                        The number of rows used for training
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph>
                                        The number of feature columns used for training
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                            </List>

                            <Paragraph Margin="20,15,0,0">
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">TRAIN</Run>
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="20,15,0,0">
                                Select Indiduvally if you want to Train | Test each security.  Select Group if you want to Train each as a group where the price and feature data are aggregated.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="20,15,0,0">
                                NOTE: Use Grouped trained Assets to Forecast any asset or single security chosen.  Individually trained assets are contract specific.  Also, the other ATM ML Applications will not forecast on an Interval not trained.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="20,15,0,0">
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">TRAIN | TEST SPLIT</Run>
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="20,15,0,0">
                                ML MODELS splits the requested data into a training set and a test set. The default split is: training data (80%) is used to train your model and the test data (20%) is held back to evaluate your model.
                                Selecting the TRAIN | TEST SPLIT button opens an array of split choices.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="20,15,0,0">
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">INTERVALS</Run>
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="20,15,0,0">
                                The Time Horizons used to Train your Model.  Each Interval will be multiplied by the (Individual or Group) relationship.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="20,15,0,0">
                                NOTE: The other ATM ML Applications will not forecast on an Interval not trained.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="0,30,0,0">
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">STEP 3 :</Run>
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="20,15,0,0">
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">FEATURE INPUT</Run>
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="20,15,0,0">
                                Each Model needs features – or datasets - to calculate. In ML MODELS, this process
                                is accomplished by selecting ‘INPUTS’  From the Input dialog.  The maximum number of inputs is 100 per mondel.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="20,15,0,0">
                                The selected dataset will be prepared or pre-processed before used to find the parameters of the model.
                                Information is: filtered for its relevance; missing values replaced with mean values; data is normalized and redundant values removed.
                            </Paragraph>

