                    <FlowDocument ColumnWidth="400" IsHyphenationEnabled="True" IsOptimalParagraphEnabled="True">

                        <Section Name="ViewHelpSection" FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11" Foreground="#BDBDBD">

                            <Paragraph Name="top">
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">ML MODELS</Run>
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph>
                                The ML MODELS Application uses automated machine learning (AutoML) to explore
                                different machine learning algorithms and settings.  This process automatically
                                selects the best algo that answers the scenario selected by the User.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="0,30,0,0">
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">WHAT IS ML MODELS</Run>
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph>
                                Automated Machine Learning, is the process of automating the time consuming, iterative
                                tasks of machine learning model development. It allows ATM Clients to build ML models
                                with high scale, efficiency, and productivity all while sustaining model quality. And
                                is based on Microsoft’s Automated ML technology.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="0,30,0,0">
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">HOW IT WORKS</Run>
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph>
                                During training, ML MODELS creates many pipelines in parallel that automatically
                                try different algorithms and parameters. The service iterates through machine learning
                                algorithms paired with feature selections, where each iteration produces a
                                model with a training score. The higher the score, the better the model is
                                considered to &quot;fit&quot; the data.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="0,30,0,0">
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">ENVIRONMENT</Run>
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph>
                                ML MODELS trains each model on the client's pc within the constraints of their computer resources (CPU, memory, and disk).
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="0,30,0,0">
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">DATA</Run>
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph>
                                Historical Price and Fundamental Data is access via Bloomberg’s Desktop API.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph>
                                ML MODELS splits the training data into a training set and a test set according to the Client’s request.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph>
                                ML MODELS then performs the following automatically:
                            </Paragraph>

                            <List>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph>
                                        Drops any feature with no useful information, which includes all values missing, the same value across all rows, or with extremely high cardinality
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph>
                                        Fills missing value cells with the default value for the datatype and appends indicator features with the same number of slots as the input column
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph>
                                        Generates additional features for high cardinality categorical features
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph>
                                        Transforms text features with very few unique values into categorical features
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                            </List>

                            <Paragraph Margin="0,30,0,0">
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">TRAINING</Run>
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph>
                                Training is an automatic process by which ML MODELS teaches the model how to answer the client's scenario question.
                                After the initial training, you can retrain models manually anytime.  The new training results will be compared
                                to the previous results.  If the latest results improve performance, the new model is used within the other
                                ATM ML Applications.  If results are not better, the previously trained model is retained.
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph Margin="0,30,0,0">
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">EVALUATE</Run>
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph>
                                The ML MODELS evaluation process:
                            </Paragraph>

                            <List>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11">
                                        Each model is evaluated for accuracy and precision based on the selected metric
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11">
                                        The best model is chosen to make future predictions
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11">
                                        Results are displayed within the ATM ML Applications
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                            </List>

                            <Paragraph Margin="0,30,0,0">
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">IMPROVE</Run>
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph>
                                If your model performance score is not as good as you want it to be, you can:
                            </Paragraph>

                            <List>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11">
                                        Train for a more extended period. With more time, the automated machine learning engine
                                        experiments with more algorithms and settings.
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                                <ListItem>
                                    <Paragraph FontFamily="Helvetica Neue" FontSize="11">
                                        Add more data. Sometimes the amount of data is not sufficient to train a high-quality machine learning model.
                                        Insufficient data is especially true with datasets that have a small number of examples.
                                    </Paragraph>
                                </ListItem>
                            </List>

                            <Paragraph Margin="0,30,0,0">
                                <Run FontWeight="Regular" Foreground="#FF8C00">DEPLOYMENT</Run>
                            </Paragraph>

                            <Paragraph>
                                Once trained, models can make predictions with input data that it has not
                                seen before and deploy these predictions to various ATM ML Applications.
                            </Paragraph>

                        </Section>

                    </FlowDocument>
                </FlowDocumentScrollViewer>

